Citation.sTitle: Vapour liquid equilibrium for the systems butane + methanol, +2-propanol, +1-butanol, +2-butanol, +2-methyl-2-propanol at 364.5K
Citation.sAbstract: Isothermal vapour liquid equilibrium measurements for the systems of butane with methanol, 2-propanol, 1-butanol, 2-butanol and 2-methyl-  2-propanol were made at 364.5K using a static total pressure apparatus. The obtained pressure temperature total composition (PTz) data were  converted into pressure temperature liquid vapour composition (PTxy) form by means of the Barker method. Error analysis was performed on  measured and calculated variables. The systems of butane with methanol and 2-propanol showed azeotropic behaviour at 364.5 K. Wilson and  NRTL parameters were regressed. The VLE measurements were compared with predictions obtained using the UNIFAC, UNIFAC-Dortmund and  COSMO-RS models.
